ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/11905/documentation

This dataset represents the production of heat from hard coal in Quebec.This is an adaptation for Quebec from the hard coal global dataset. Only time period, annual production volume and heating value have been modified. Uncertainties have been adjusted accordingly.;;The stoker boiler is assumed to fire egg coal with quality between long-flame coal and fat coal. The heating value (28.9 MJ/kg) and the composition of the coal are average values available from the literature. The emission data are also taken from literature reporting measurements performed at the end of the 1980s in Germany. Size distribution of particles has been estimated on the basis of recent information from EPA. Emissions of trace elements  were calculated using the ash content in the coal and average transfer coefficients for coal power plants with ash retention of 98 %, as first approximation. With the assumption that coal is stored in a dry storage, no leaching is considered. Possible emissions to water during operation of the boiler are not included for missing information.

Activity starts with the combustion of the fuel.

This activity ends with 1MJ of heat produced by the furnace. 
This dataset includes:

-fuel inputs;
-emissions due to combustion of fuel;
-inputs needed for combustion (electricity);
-by-products of combustion
-infrastructures
